Topic of project - Calculator

 1. Introduction
     A calculator is a computational tool used to perform arithmetic operations such as addition,
     subtraction, multiplication, and division. This project demonstrates the design and implementation
     of a calculator application using programming concepts.
 2. Objectives- To develop a simple and user friendly calculator.- To perform basic arithmetic operations.- To understand event-driven programming and logic development.- To create modular and maintainable code.
 3. Tools & Technologies Used
    a.Programming Language: Python 
    b.IDE: VS Code
    c.OS: Windows
 4. System Requirements
 Hardware: Intel i3 or above, 4GB RAM, 100MB storage
 Software: Programming IDE, Language runtime
 5. Methodology
   a. Requirement Analysis
   b. Design (Flowchart, Algorithm)
   c. Implementation- 
   d.Testing- Deployment
 6. Algorithm
    a. Start
    b. Read input numbers
    c. Read operator
    d. Perform operation based on operator
    e. Display result
    f. End
 8. Conclusion
 The calculator project provides an understanding of logical operations, coding structure, and user
 interaction. It serves as a foundation for advanced calculators.
 9. Future Scope-
    a.Scientific calculations
    b. Graphing features
    c.Memory functions
    d.Mobile version
